)

is exclusively known from sphecids. The reported host species build nests in different substrates like sand, mud, dead wood or stalks. After deposition of the eggs, the nests are supplied with different paralyzed insects or spiders which serve as food for the offspring (
Witt 1998
). The nests probably are suitable habitats for mites as they contain enough material which could become moldy. However, no scutacarids have been reported from nests so far,
